summary: Stop being so overdramatic over what idols wear or how they show their bodies off.
body:
Hey guys, let me say something real quick- …

Stop being so overdramatic over what idols wear or how they show their bodies off.

They are beautiful human beings and they work hard for their body. So why not show them off?

They’re not like stripping to the point of being completely naked. So fuck off.

Because that’s how we love them, right?

Confident.

Thank you.

summary:
Hi everyone, I have an announcement about this blog: I'm not going to be answering copy-paste asks anymore. 
I talked about my...
body:
Hi everyone, I have an announcement about this blog: I’m not going to be answering copy-paste asks anymore.

I talked about my stance on copy-paste anons in an earlier ask - I’m not offended by them, I can see why they copy-paste asks - and even though that is still true, the way I see it, I manage this blog because I want to destress and casually discuss KM and not because I want to become a big KM analysis blog, so I don’t need to spend my time answering generic asks when I could spend it doing something else. While I do receive some interesting copy-paste asks, many of them are just very generic questions that could be answered by any KM blog on here, and many of these questions don’t even need more than one person’s answer, so I’d rather not waste my time on these type of asks. I might still answer copy-paste asks if (a) I don’t know that it’s a copy-paste ask, (b) the question is particularly interesting, and © the asker goes off anon, in which case I probably will answer because I don’t like to ignore asks from non-anons.

If you sent me a copy-paste ask in the last couple of days, I probably ignored it and this is why, so please don’t take it personally. Have a great day! :)
